summary: Completed comprehensive testing of StealthTrack app with focus on shumard.js renaming and new delete functionality. Backend APIs are 100% functional including the new DELETE endpoint. Frontend UI works correctly with proper script snippet, no skeleton flash, and modal interactions. Tracking script successfully captures form data and creates contacts.

integration_issues.issue: Delete button/functionality not accessible from contact detail modal or table rows

passed_tests: GET /api/shumard.js returns 200 with valid JavaScript and [Shumard] logs
GET /api/tracker.js returns 404 (old name no longer exists)
DELETE /api/contacts/{contact_id} returns 204 and contact is removed
GET /api/contacts returns list of contacts (52 contacts)
GET /api/contacts/{contact_id} returns contact detail with visits array
POST /api/track/pageview captures page view and creates contact
POST /api/track/lead captures email and phone fields
POST /api/track/registration captures name/email/phone and logs visit
Dashboard loads without skeleton flash on reload
Contact row clicks open detail modal with Overview/Attribution/URL History tabs
Contact detail modal shows phone number field in Overview tab
Shumard tracking script successfully captures form fields and creates contacts
Console logging works with [Shumard] prefix for all events
action_item_for_main_agent: Add delete button to ContactDetailModal component to allow users to delete contacts via UI. The DELETE API endpoint works but is not accessible from the frontend interface.
